         <abstract>
            <p>For Tikhonov's regularization of ill-posed linear integral equations, numerical accuracy is estimated by a modulus of convergence, for which upper and lower bounds are obtained. Applications are made to the backward heat equation, to harmonic continuation, and to numerical differentiation.</p>
         </abstract>
